In this article, Vice President Mike Pence discusses the Graham-Cassidy healthcare bill, which aims to repeal and replace Obamacare. Pence argues that the bill gives states more freedom and flexibility to design healthcare solutions that will lower costs and expand access to coverage. He criticizes the centralized control of healthcare under Obamacare and emphasizes the importance of state governments in managing healthcare systems. Pence encourages the citizens of Alaska to support the bill by contacting their senators. The article concludes with a light-hearted exchange between Pence and the radio show host.